\v 1 \w A|strong="H3068"\w* \w message|strong="H4853"\w* \w about|strong="H4853"\w* \w the|strong="H3372"\w* \w desert|strong="H4057"\w* \w by|strong="H3372"\w* \w the|strong="H3372"\w* \w sea|strong="H3220"\w*.\f + \fr 21:1 \ft “Desert by the sea,” usually taken to refer to Babylon. Although there is no literal sea nearby, the large Euphrates River can be referred to as a “sea” in the same way the Nile is described in \xt 18:2\ft , \xt 19:5\ft .\f* \w Like|strong="H4057"\w* \w storm|strong="H5492"\w* winds passing \w through|strong="H2498"\w* \w the|strong="H3372"\w* \w Negev|strong="H5045"\w*, something \w is|strong="H4057"\w* coming from \w the|strong="H3372"\w* \w desert|strong="H4057"\w*, from \w a|strong="H3068"\w* land \w of|strong="H4057"\w* terror—  
